Subject: http://semanticscience.org/resource/Fictional

Subject: http://semanticscience.org/resource/Gene-diseaseAssociationLinkedWithGeneticVariation
Object: gene-disease association linked with genetic variation

Subject: http://semanticscience.org/resource/Genome
Object: A genome is a collection of nucleic acids.

Subject: http://semanticscience.org/resource/List

Subject: http://semanticscience.org/resource/IncreasedDurationOfProcessFromIncreasedRegulation
Object: increased duration of process from increased regulation

Subject: http://semanticscience.org/resource/DecreasedSpatialExtentOfProcessFromDecreasedRegulation
Object: decreased spatial extent of process from decreased regulation

Object: ability of electric current to flow through a material

Object: to contain is the capability to bound or constrain a physical entity in some site.

Subject: http://semanticscience.org/resource/DatabaseRow

Subject: http://semanticscience.org/resource/ToInvestigate

Subject: http://semanticscience.org/resource/Allotrope

Subject: http://semanticscience.org/resource/Count

Subject: http://semanticscience.org/resource/PeerReviewedArticle

Subject: http://semanticscience.org/resource/Frequency
Object: The rate of occurrence of some periodic event.

Subject: http://purl.org/ontology/bibo/Map
Object: A graphical depiction of geographic features.

Subject: http://semanticscience.org/resource/ToTransport
Object: to transport is the capability to displace a material from one location to another.

Subject: http://materialsmine.org/ns/Density
Object: degree of consistency measured by the quantity of mass per unit volume

Subject: http://purl.org/dc/terms/isReferencedBy
Object: Used to relate a reference citation to a bibliographic resource.

Subject: http://materialsmine.org/ns/CrystallizationTemperature

Subject: http://semanticscience.org/resource/isMeasurementValueOf

Subject: http://semanticscience.org/resource/CompositionalQuality
Object: composition quality is a quality that describes its composition or anatomy.

Subject: http://semanticscience.org/resource/BiologicalSex
Object: biological sex is the quality of a biological organism based on reproductive function or organs.

Subject: http://semanticscience.org/resource/Matrix

Subject: http://semanticscience.org/resource/Recipe
Object: A recipe is a set of instructions that describe how to prepare or make something.

Subject: http://purl.org/ontology/bibo/subsequentLegalDecision
